							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/fionawarnick/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WarnickFiona_creditJanelleIckes_LoRes-e1714586285679-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WarnickFiona_creditJanelleIckes_LoRes-e1714586285679-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Fiona Warnick" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/fionawarnick/">Fiona Warnick</a></h6>
										Fiona Warnick grew up in Western Massachusetts and holds a BA in Creative Writing from Oberlin College, where she won the Emma Howell Poetry Prize. Her debut novel <em>The Skunks</em> is available via Tin House. She teaches preschool in Providence, RI.																			</div>
